1
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:09,625
[car horn honks]

2
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:10,625
[GUY 1A]
We're changing the specs

3
00:00:10,708 --> 00:00:11,958
this close to the deadline?

4
00:00:12,041 --> 00:00:13,166
[KURATA]
Huh?

5
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,208
Those morons in sales
didn't even ask us!

6
00:00:15,291 --> 00:00:17,166
I've already hit a hundred
hours of overtime

7
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:18,291
and I'm tapped out.

8
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:19,833
Hell, it's not like
we have a choice.

9
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:21,125
They got us by the balls.

10
00:00:21,208 --> 00:00:22,916
Relax, guys,
I've got this covered.

11
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:23,958
[GUY 1A]
Huh?

12
00:00:24,041 --> 00:00:25,500
[GUY 1B]
How you gonna do that?

13
00:00:25,583 --> 00:00:28,875
Well, they did hire me
for my skills as a programmer.

14
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,833
Unfortunately,
we don't have enough time

15
00:00:32,916 --> 00:00:35,041
to do the job the right way.

16
00:00:35,125 --> 00:00:37,333
I'll just give it
the old college try.

17
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,708
[music plays]

18
00:00:40,791 --> 00:00:41,916
[KURATA]
Oh my gosh!

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,041
A neutral grade
Mephisto Mark Two!

20
00:00:44,125 --> 00:00:45,875
I didn't know it was out!

21
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:48,250
I can't believe they actually
carry the High Divine models

22
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:50,416
in a place like this! Nice!

23
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,916
[laughing]

24
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
[GUY 1C] I thought I'd
be looking for a new job.

25
00:00:55,083 --> 00:00:57,000
Kurata's a freakin' wizard.

26
00:00:57,083 --> 00:00:59,458
[GUY 1A] If by wizard
you mean nerd, then yes.

27
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:01,458
[GUY 1B]
Yeah, he's a mega otaku.

28
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:02,916
Apparently, he's filled a room

29
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,833
in his apartment
with plastic models.

30
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:06,125
[GUY 1A]
Like, girly models?

31
00:01:06,208 --> 00:01:08,208
[GUY 1C]
No, like anime giant robots.

32
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:09,916
[GUY 1B]
I don't care if he's an otaku!

33
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,833
Mr. Kurata's my hero!

34
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:14,416
His programming's
the stuff of legend!

35
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,666
[GUY 1C]
Well, he's a genius.

36
00:01:19,541 --> 00:01:21,208
[car horn honks]

37
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:27,375
[crosswalk beeping]

38
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:32,750
[car engine revs]

39
00:01:35,666 --> 00:01:38,541
[KURATA]
So, the models I bought today,

40
00:01:38,625 --> 00:01:40,375
the pile I have at home,

41
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:42,958
and the ones that
will come after this.

42
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:46,083
I'll never get to build them.

43
00:01:46,166 --> 00:01:48,750
This isn't fair!

44
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:50,875
[BIRD caws]

45
00:01:51,416 --> 00:02:01,041
♪

46
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:03,625
How is His Highness
faring these days, Father?

47
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:04,875
Well, I hope.

48
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:07,541
King Ambrosius is
as healthy as ever, dear.

49
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:10,250
Keeping his strength is
part of his duty, after all.

50
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:13,791
The prosperity of our fair
Fremmevilla hinges on his might.

51
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:15,708
And, with the ever-rising
threat of demon beasts,

52
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:17,916
that might will soon be tested.

53
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,541
I think he knows it, too.

54
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:22,083
He just presented the Knight
Runners of Laihiala Academy

55
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:25,791
with a large sum of money
and a rather splendid speech.

56
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:28,416
It's his way of telling us
to raise more Knight Runners,

57
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,791
and do it quickly.

58
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:32,291
That husband of yours
will have his hands full.

59
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:35,125
[SELESTINA] There's no need
to worry about Mathias, Father.

60
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:36,583
[gasps]

61
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:39,708
[LAURI] Perhaps not,
but I can't help worrying

62
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:41,416
about my grandson there.

63
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,875
I can understand that.
Ernesti isn't as developed

64
00:02:43,958 --> 00:02:46,666
as the other boys
his age. He's small.

65
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,083
But I can't shake the feeling

66
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:50,375
that he's destined
for greatness.

67
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:53,250
[BOTH gasp]

68
00:02:58,291 --> 00:03:00,083
Ah!
[hollers]

69
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:01,833
[LAURI grunts]

70
00:03:08,041 --> 00:03:11,208
Curse your wretched kind!

71
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:13,500
[grunting]

72
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:22,625
[LAURI yells]

73
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:27,666
[LAURI grunts]

74
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,416
[gasps]

75
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:41,375
Ernie, no!

76
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:45,916
Ernie!

77
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:50,625
[guttural exhale]

78
00:03:53,916 --> 00:03:55,791
[ERNESTI gasps]

79
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:03,958
[KURATA]
No way. Is that...?

80
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,541
[ERNESTI]
A robot?

81
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,666
[MATHIAS]
Stay back! We'll handle this!

82
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,625
[LAURI]
That sounded like Mathias!

83
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:25,583
[MATHIAS grunting]

84
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,041
[MATHIAS groans]

85
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:31,916
[grunting]

86
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,416
[MATHIAS yells]

87
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,916
[MATHIAS grunting]

88
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:55,250
[yells]

89
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:05,083
[grunting]

90
00:05:15,041 --> 00:05:16,500
[ERNESTI gasps]

91
00:05:17,541 --> 00:05:19,583
[MATHIAS] Looks like
no one's worse for wear.

92
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:23,208
Yes, thanks to your
impeccable timing.

93
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:26,375
[MATHIAS] I heard demon beasts
were attacking the road.

94
00:05:26,458 --> 00:05:28,791
Sorry, I came
as fast as I could.

95
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,416
[gasps]

96
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:33,291
[MATHIAS]
Ernie! Are you okay?

97
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,791
[ERNESTI]
A real robot!

98
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,208
What's a robot?

99
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:39,125
Do you mean
the Silhouette Knight?

100
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:41,083
Is that what
you call this thing?

101
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:44,625
[MATHIAS] Uh-huh. Each one
is powered by magic.

102
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:46,250
[LAURI]
Do you like it, my boy?

103
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,083
When you're older,
perhaps <i>you</i> could be

104
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,375
a Knight Runner yourself!

105
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:52,958
[ERNESTI]
Amazing.

106
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:54,750
So, if I become
a Knight Runner,

107
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:57,041
I can pilot a Silhouette Knight?

108
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:59,500
You would have to learn
magic and swordsmanship.

109
00:05:59,583 --> 00:06:01,916
But, I know you can do it.

110
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,166
[KURATA] I get it. I was reborn
into this world for this.

111
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:09,833
To meet these
magnificent robots!

112
00:06:09,916 --> 00:06:13,458
I'll do it! I'll be
the best Knight Runner ever!

113
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,250
[SELESTINA]
It is the Occidental Year 1268.

114
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,791
The Kingdom of Fremmevilla
is constantly under threat

115
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:22,000
by roaming demon beasts.

116
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:24,916
Our story begins near
the capital of Kankkunen

117
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,041
in the Academy City of Laihiala,

118
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:30,000
where young Ernesti
starts his journey.

119
00:06:38,791 --> 00:06:41,375
[SELESTINA] The slow, repetitive
training and constant study

120
00:06:41,458 --> 00:06:45,625
that most children would despise
was no problem for Ernesti.

121
00:06:45,708 --> 00:06:48,041
Instead, he immersed himself.

122
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:50,750
For him, every lesson
learned was another step

123
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:53,500
towards piloting
a Silhouette Knight.

124
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,083
[ERNESTI] I'll add emission
and enhancement spells

125
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,333
to the basic
wind spell structure.

126
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,000
And execute!

127
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:05,875
[ERNESTI] I see! Magic works
the same way that programs do.

128
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,458
[gasps]

129
00:07:07,541 --> 00:07:10,041
[SELESTINA] The next three years
passed in the blink of an eye.

130
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:13,541
[ADELTRUD] You're so slow, kid!
They're going to find us!

131
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:15,291
[ARCHID]
Don't be in such a hurry!

132
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:17,208
[ADELTRUD] He's supposed to
be here in the morning.

133
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:19,458
I don't want to see him!

134
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:22,166
But Mom really wants us
to meet him. What's up?

135
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,125
He's not my father!
And he never will be.

136
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:26,541
Noble, or not!

137
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:28,958
But he is a noble. We have to.

138
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:31,125
Fine, then you can stay here.

139
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:33,583
Nah. Someone's got to watch you.

140
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:36,291
Hey! Don't say it like th--

141
00:07:36,375 --> 00:07:37,833
Addy!

142
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,583
[ADELTRUD screams]

143
00:07:48,583 --> 00:07:50,333
[ADELTRUD]
You saved me!

144
00:07:50,416 --> 00:07:53,416
You're welcome. My name's
Ernesti, by the way.

145
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:55,250
Wait, you're a boy?

146
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:57,000
You're lucky
I was training here.

147
00:07:57,083 --> 00:08:00,791
Be careful, the rooftops are
slippery in the morning. Bye.

148
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:04,041
Hold on! If it's so dangerous,
why are you up here?

149
00:08:04,125 --> 00:08:09,416
Suspicious! Also, I refuse
to believe a boy's that cute!

150
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,291
[SELESTINA] This was Ernesti's
first meeting with his

151
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:15,791
future lifelong friends,
Archid and Adeltrud.

152
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:17,583
You used magic, didn't you?

153
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:19,708
Do you think you could
teach us some, too?

154
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,291
Spell-craft isn't something
you can just pick up.

155
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,750
First, you have to develop
your mana, or "magic power,"

156
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,250
and that takes lots of training.

157
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,708
I'll do it!

158
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,458
If you're serious about it,
I don't mind teaching you,

159
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:30,916
but it will be tough.

160
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,541
So cute! Listen to you,
sounding all reliable!

161
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,541
Mistress! I found them, ma'am!
They're on the roof!

162
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,541
--Uh oh.
--We'd better go.

163
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:41,083
See you tomorrow morning?

164
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:42,541
Sure.

165
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:46,666
[SELESTINA]
Ernesti's hometown, Laihiala,

166
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:50,208
had a singular purpose within
the Kingdom of Fremmevilla.

167
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:52,125
To train the Knight Runners,

168
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:55,250
and produce the Silhouette
Knights they would pilot.

169
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:58,833
Of course, Ernesti's dream
was to become a pilot himself.

170
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:02,500
So, when the time was right,
he joined the academy.

171
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:09,958
[TEACHER 1A]
In those booklets,

172
00:09:10,041 --> 00:09:13,000
you'll find a comprehensive
guide to all of your classes.

173
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,250
Please find the section marked
"Elementary School" and--

174
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:19,083
Fundamentals Silhouette Design?
I can't wait to take that class!

175
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:20,750
Mr. Echevalier.

176
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:23,208
That course is for
middle school students.

177
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:24,541
For now, we'll be focusing on

178
00:09:24,625 --> 00:09:26,625
the development
of your magic power.

179
00:09:26,708 --> 00:09:28,750
I understand that, sir.
The thing is,

180
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:31,541
I want to be a Knight Runner
as soon as possible!

181
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:35,166
Unfortunately, there are two
fundamentals you sorely lack.

182
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:39,583
A complete knowledge
of the basics, and stature.

183
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:44,291
C'mon, Ernie.
Try not to let it get to you.

184
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,958
Of course, the seats
would be designed

185
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:49,083
for full-grown adults.
I should have realized that.

186
00:09:49,166 --> 00:09:50,875
I need to get big, and fast!

187
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:54,583
No way! You have to stay
cute and small forever!

188
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:56,458
Unless there's another way.

189
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:57,916
[gasps]
That's it!

190
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,250
If I can't change myself,

191
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,333
I'll change the
Silhouette Knights instead!

192
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:02,625
[BOTH]
What do you mean?

193
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,708
I'll just build one
that I can fit in!

194
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:07,208
--I think he's gone crazy.
--Build a Knight?

195
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:10,958
Of course, why wouldn't I?
Customizing's the best part!

196
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:13,458
Though, if we're talking
a redesign from the ground up,

197
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:15,166
that makes having
a complete understanding

198
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,333
of the design
principles crucial.

199
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:18,916
I need to get out
of that magic class

200
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,750
and into middle school
courses pronto!

201
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,125
[BOY 1A]
Na-na-na-na-naa-naaah!

202
00:10:22,208 --> 00:10:23,500
--[BOY 1C] Hurry up, stumpy!
--[BOY 1A] Come get it!

203
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:25,041
[BATSON] You'll be sorry
when I catch you!

204
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,291
Give it back!

205
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,458
[BOY 1A, BOY 1B laugh]

206
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:29,333
This hammers too good
for a dirty dwarf!

207
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:30,625
It's ours now!

208
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:32,166
Guess you're
out of luck, freak!

209
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:33,750
Hey, what's going on?

210
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,541
They think that they can
get away with picking on me

211
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:37,708
because my legs are too short
to keep up with them.

212
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,125
Those dumb jerks!

213
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:42,083
I saved up for months
to afford that hammer!

214
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:43,208
They can't have it!

215
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:45,458
Wait a second!

216
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:48,291
[ERNESTI] Sorry. I was
wondering what you study here.

217
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:49,833
You kidding? I'm a dwarf,

218
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,625
what do you think
I'm gonna study?

219
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:54,500
My family's been
Knightsmiths for generations!

220
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:56,291
Please, forgive my ignorance.

221
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:57,958
I happen to have
a great deal of respect

222
00:10:58,041 --> 00:11:00,208
for anyone involved with
Silhouette Knights.

223
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:03,041
If you're interested, I think
I can help you out here.

224
00:11:03,125 --> 00:11:05,250
[PEOPLE chattering]

225
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,958
[BOY 1A, 1B, 1C]
♪ Batson's a slow poke! ♪

226
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,083
♪ His brains are
full of egg yolk! ♪

227
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:10,875
When I get my hands of them...

228
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:12,375
Let's do it, you two.

229
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:13,833
[BOTH]
Okay!

230
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:19,000
[ALL]
Aero Batson! Ready. Fire!

231
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:20,958
[BATSON yells]

232
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:22,625
[BOY 1A, 1B, 1C groan]

233
00:11:24,708 --> 00:11:26,875
Okay, who the heck are you guys?

234
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:29,750
And how did you learn
a high spell like that?

235
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:33,666
[BATSON] Hold on. This kid
mastered the fundamentals

236
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:36,000
on his own <i>and</i> taught you two?

237
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:38,625
Yup! Impressive, isn't it?

238
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:42,625
[ERNESTI]
Hmmm.

239
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:44,958
Don't you think these rods
are a little awkward?

240
00:11:45,041 --> 00:11:46,208
[ARCHID, BATSON, ADELTRUD]
Huh?

241
00:11:46,291 --> 00:11:48,208
I understand why we need
to attach this catalyst

242
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:50,791
to a device in order to focus
and transform our mana.

243
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:54,000
A rod is the most practical form
to produce magical phenomena.

244
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:57,166
But I can't help thinking
the design is missing something.

245
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,958
[BATSON]
Looks like you've used it a lot.

246
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:00,666
But only for the usual stuff.

247
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:02,041
[BATSON]
Usual?

248
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:04,000
My point is, Knight Runners
face times when

249
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:06,375
a more precise control
of magic is needed.

250
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:08,208
Maybe changing the shape
of the basic rod

251
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:10,916
could accomplish that. May I?

252
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:13,791
Something like this.

253
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:16,291
--I don't get it.
--Yeah, looks weird.

254
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:18,500
This would give the rod
more utility.

255
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:20,833
It combines the power
of a sword to cut enemies

256
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:22,750
with a gun that fires magic.

257
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,250
Uh? Interestin' idea
you got there, kid.

258
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:26,541
I like it.

259
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:28,041
If you can try
to make one for me,

260
00:12:28,125 --> 00:12:29,875
I'll show you what it can do.

261
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:33,916
Hell, with confidence like that
I'd be crazy to say no, right?

262
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,958
Fireball blast!

263
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:43,333
Seems we have some talent
in this year's batch,

264
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:44,625
wouldn't you say?

265
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:45,916
T'would seem so.

266
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,833
Of course, the problem
with talented students

267
00:12:47,916 --> 00:12:50,333
is that some of them
are painfully aware of it.

268
00:12:50,416 --> 00:12:53,583
'Scuse me! May I
make a request, sir?

269
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:55,625
Yes, what is it, Echevalier?

270
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:57,208
If I showed that
my current skills

271
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:59,416
are far beyond
the contents of this course,

272
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,958
could I skip magic
fundamentals and go

273
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:02,583
straight to middle school?

274
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:04,375
Young man, I highly
doubt you could produce

275
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:06,125
such fantastic results.

276
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:08,083
Then, allow me
to prove it to you, sir.

277
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:09,958
If I do, there's a class
during this period

278
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:11,750
I'd like to switch to.

279
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,291
[TEACHER 1A] Being the
headmaster's grandson

280
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,666
doesn't give you the right
to special treatment.

281
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,166
[ERNESTI]
I don't want any.

282
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:18,500
I'd like you to
make the decision based

283
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:20,541
solely off my abilities.

284
00:13:21,458 --> 00:13:23,541
[TEACHER 1A] You do
understand that being excused

285
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,583
from Magical Fundamentals
would mean you possess

286
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:27,291
the same level of mana
and knowledge

287
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:29,125
as a middle school student?

288
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,625
I do, sir.

289
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:34,625
Very well. We'll see
why you're so confident.

290
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:36,583
Take your position.

291
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,250
[ALL gasp]

292
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:43,166
--[BOY 1A] What is that?
--[GIRL 1A] A rod?

293
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:45,416
[BOY 1A]
Looks weird.

294
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,625
First, a Piercing Lance.

295
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:03,291
Followed by a full-powered
Thundering Gale!

296
00:14:07,958 --> 00:14:09,083
[ALL gasp]

297
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,333
He did it!

298
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:12,000
--[ARCHID] Yeah!
--[ADELTRUD laughs]

299
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,750
Did I meet the requirement?

300
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,708
If so, could I
be excused, please?

301
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:22,958
[SELESTINA]
By the end of the day,

302
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:25,250
the rumor that
an elementary school student

303
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,833
had performed a high spell
and was granted the right

304
00:14:27,916 --> 00:14:29,666
to take middle school courses

305
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:32,250
had spread throughout
the entire academy.

306
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,416
However, no one could have
known that this was

307
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:37,250
merely the first of
many steps Ernesti would take

308
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:40,416
toward his destiny
of changing the kingdom,

309
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:42,625
and the world, forever.

310
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:48,541
[BATSON] The structure
of an Ether Reactor?

311
00:14:48,625 --> 00:14:51,541
[ERNESTI] Yes. What they call
a magical energy transformer.

312
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:54,125
It's the engine that forms the
core of a Silhouette Knight,

313
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:56,208
or it's "heart."

314
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:58,750
Without an understanding of it,
there's no way you could be

315
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:00,875
a master of a Silouette Knight.

316
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:03,000
[BATSON] Well, yeah.
Why do you think the design

317
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:04,750
is a national secret?

318
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,458
[ERNESTI] Even a
Knightsmith like your father

319
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:08,208
doesn't know it?

320
00:15:08,291 --> 00:15:10,750
[BATSON] We're not high enough
level for that kind of stuff.

321
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,583
We don't even know
what the reactor's made of,

322
00:15:12,666 --> 00:15:14,833
--let alone how to build one.
--[ERNESTI] Mmm.

323
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:16,666
Are you really planning
to make your own unit

324
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,125
from scratch, Ernie?

325
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:19,583
Of course I am!

326
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:21,250
[BATSON] It's been a hundred
years since the Kingdom's

327
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:24,250
standard Silhouette Knight,
the Kaldatoah, was introduced.

328
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,500
And there have been
no advancements since then!

329
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,458
Even the Solodreahs
we use are made from

330
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:30,458
300-year-old schematics.

331
00:15:30,541 --> 00:15:32,583
You can't make something new
and expect it to--

332
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:35,291
Don't worry. It will work.

333
00:15:35,375 --> 00:15:36,708
Ernie! Get down here quick,

334
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:38,500
we're about to head out!

335
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:39,875
We'll talk more when I get back.

336
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:41,291
Be careful out there.

337
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:42,666
Even with the
high school's protection,

338
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,083
a demon beast
is nothing to sneeze at.

339
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:52,791
♪

340
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:00,916
[SELESTINA] Laihiala Academy
prizes field exercises

341
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,791
and combat training.

342
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:04,291
The middle and
high school students

343
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:07,000
in the Knight curriculum
headed to a nearby forest,

344
00:16:07,083 --> 00:16:09,458
where a herd of relatively
small demon beasts

345
00:16:09,541 --> 00:16:11,416
were supposed to live.

346
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:15,291
[DIETRICH sigh]
I was expecting demon beasts,

347
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:17,833
not a pleasant country stroll.

348
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:19,750
I wasn't trained
to fight boredom.

349
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:23,541
Quit your whining, D.
I'd like to keep my sanity.

350
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:26,000
[DIETRICH] Hey, what's wrong
with telling the truth?

351
00:16:26,083 --> 00:16:27,916
[EDGAR]
Helvi, D! Enough!

352
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,833
There's more
to training than combat.

353
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:32,250
Long stretches of marching
will test your resolve

354
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,791
as much as any battle.

355
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,541
[DIETRICH] Spoken like a true
masochist, fearless leader.

356
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,375
At least one of us is happy.

357
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,708
[ARCHID]
Mm-mmm! That was perfect!

358
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:42,791
I'm stuffed!

359
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:44,916
I hope so.
You ate like a wild boar.

360
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,250
[STEFANIA]
You've already finished dinner?

361
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,375
You must have had
quite the appetite.

362
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:52,291
--Uh. Hi, Sister Stefa--
--Council President.

363
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:54,166
[STEFANIA]
"Big Sister" will do fine.

364
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,583
We may have different mothers,

365
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:58,083
but our father's blood
still runs through each of us.

366
00:16:59,125 --> 00:17:00,833
I take it you're
the gifted Ernesti

367
00:17:00,916 --> 00:17:02,208
I've heard so much about?

368
00:17:02,291 --> 00:17:03,958
--Yes?
--[ADELTRUD] Uh?

369
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:06,041
[STEFANIA] Don't be surprised.
Everyone at the academy's

370
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:08,250
heard of you.
Though, I'm not sure why

371
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,500
you want to advance
in grade so quickly.

372
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:13,375
What about the Silhouette
Knights is so enticing?

373
00:17:13,458 --> 00:17:15,791
[ERNESTI] That would take
a while to explain.

374
00:17:15,875 --> 00:17:18,458
You're a little on the
eccentric side, aren't you?

375
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:20,625
Big Sis. It's not weird!

376
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:22,833
[STEFANIA]
I didn't mean anything by it.

377
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:24,416
I simply have
a fondness for kids

378
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,083
with looks and intelligence.

379
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:27,541
[ADELTRUD]
Uuh!

380
00:17:27,625 --> 00:17:29,416
[STEFANIA] Sadly, the third-
years have night training,

381
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,083
so I must be off.

382
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:33,291
I hope, someday, I'll truly
get to know your mind.

383
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:34,875
[yells]

384
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:37,000
[STEFANIA giggles]

385
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:42,958
--[ADELTRUD] Hmm!
--[ARCHID] Sorry, Ernie.

386
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:44,958
Guess I hoped this
would never come up,

387
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:46,666
so I kept it from you.

388
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:49,083
The council president's dad,
Marquis Joachim Selati,

389
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:51,208
happens to be our dad, too.

390
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:53,708
He and our mom had a thing,
but she isn't a noble,

391
00:17:53,791 --> 00:17:55,625
so they couldn't marry.

392
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:59,000
Which means Addy and I...
well, we're...

393
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:01,791
Excluded from the line
of noble succession, right?

394
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:03,666
I understand the situation.

395
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,666
Just tell me
what you need me to do.

396
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:07,041
"To do"?

397
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:09,041
Attack head on? Ignore her?

398
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:10,791
Or, ambush her at night?

399
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:12,458
Ambush. It's safer.

400
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:14,208
Wait! None of those!

401
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:15,875
Where'd that even come from?

402
00:18:15,958 --> 00:18:17,166
If my friends are in trouble,

403
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:19,291
I have no intention
of ignoring that.

404
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:21,375
Whenever you need help,
I'll be there.

405
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,916
[gasps]
That really means a lot.

406
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,208
You're a hell of
a friend, Ernie.

407
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,416
[gasps, giggles]

408
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,583
Giant robots
really are the best!

409
00:18:33,666 --> 00:18:35,458
Merely looking at it
brings me peace.

410
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,375
Every family should have one!

411
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:39,125
I heard that the academy's
Silhouette Knights

412
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:40,916
were passed down
from the military,

413
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,125
but this one's undergone
some extensive customization.

414
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:47,166
You almost can't tell
it started out as a Solodreah!

415
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:48,708
[EDGAR] The Earlcumber and I
have been together

416
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,333
for nearly two years.

417
00:18:50,416 --> 00:18:53,708
I've made a few special
modifications myself.

418
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:55,083
[ERNESTI]
Good to see you, Edgar.

419
00:18:55,166 --> 00:18:57,666
Are you going out on patrol
tonight all by yourself?

420
00:18:57,750 --> 00:19:00,916
Uh-huh. My partner,
Dietrich's, being difficult.

421
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,375
You seem almost
as passionate about

422
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:03,958
Silhouette Knights as I am.

423
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:07,250
Really? I guess I can see
why you would think that.

424
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,833
It's important to me.

425
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:10,916
Earlcumber isn't just my weapon.

426
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,750
It's my armor.
My irreplaceable partner.

427
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,250
I'm so envious!

428
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:18,541
I wish I could speed up time
and get a partner of my own.

429
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:20,333
[EDGAR]
Well, wanna hop in?

430
00:19:20,416 --> 00:19:21,458
[ERNESTI gasps]

431
00:19:21,541 --> 00:19:23,000
[EDGAR]
I can't let you pilot it,

432
00:19:23,083 --> 00:19:24,208
but you can sit in it.

433
00:19:24,291 --> 00:19:26,708
Ooh! Yes, please!

434
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:30,750
[gasps]

435
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,375
[chuckles]

436
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:39,208
[gasps, laughs]

437
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,958
[EDGAR] I figured you
wouldn't reach the stirrup.

438
00:19:44,041 --> 00:19:45,916
--[ERNESTI gasps]
--Are you okay?

439
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,875
[ERNESTI]
Great! Better than great!

440
00:19:47,958 --> 00:19:49,875
I'm actually sitting in a robot!

441
00:19:49,958 --> 00:19:52,458
What's a robot?
I've never heard of it.

442
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:55,083
What every man dreams of!

443
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:07,250
[MONSTERS chattering]

444
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:09,291
[alarm rings]

445
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:10,916
Addy, wake up!

446
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,458
Aww. Thanks, Ernie.

447
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,166
[ERNESTI]
What are you doing?

448
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,375
A large group of demon beasts
attacked the third-years

449
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:17,875
during their night exercises.

450
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:19,166
We're getting out of here!

451
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:20,791
First and second years,
leave your things

452
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:23,166
and get in the
transports immediately!

453
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,750
High school students,
advance in your

454
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:27,333
Silhouette Knights
and cover their retreat!

455
00:20:27,416 --> 00:20:29,541
[DIETRICH grunts]
Hm.

456
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,625
[horse neighs]

457
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,791
We'll make it out
of here alive, won't we?

458
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:47,208
There's no way to know.

459
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:49,416
My uncle died
in this same situation.

460
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,791
[TEACHER 1A]
No talking!

461
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:54,083
I hope Big Sis is okay.

462
00:20:54,166 --> 00:20:56,916
Stefania.

463
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,708
Go! We're all in!

464
00:20:58,791 --> 00:20:59,916
[ERNESTI]
Sir!

465
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,166
--[ERNESTI] I have a request!
--[hollers]

466
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:03,125
And I thought this night
couldn't get any worse.

467
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:09,166
[STEFANIA grunts]

468
00:21:14,625 --> 00:21:16,500
[MONSTER roars]

469
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:19,875
[BOY 1E]
Help me!

470
00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:22,166
--[GIRL 1C grunts]
--[MONSTER 1B roars]

471
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:27,375
[STEFANIA] Why are there
so many beasts here?

472
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:31,333
[MONSTERS grunting]

473
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:32,791
[gasps]

474
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:35,958
[roars]

475
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:39,666
[ERNESTI yells]

476
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:40,708
[MONSTER 1C groans]

477
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:42,541
Is that Ernesti?

478
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:45,916
--[ARCHID] You okay, President?
--Don't worry!

479
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,750
[BOTH]
We'll handle this!

480
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:49,541
[ARCHID]
Sonic Blade!

481
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:51,750
Riot Sparrow!

482
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,708
[MONSTERS roar]

483
00:21:53,791 --> 00:21:55,791
My siblings. You came for me.

484
00:21:55,875 --> 00:21:58,208
Yeah and we brought
the big guns with us!

485
00:21:59,958 --> 00:22:02,916
Sorry we're late!
Now, let the pros go to work!

486
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,541
Guair! Do your thing!

487
00:22:08,541 --> 00:22:11,000
[MONSTERS roaring]

488
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:13,666
[GIRL 1E, GIRL 1D gasp]

489
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:15,458
[EDGAR]
Move to a safe distance!

490
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:17,583
Helvi, clear a path
for them to retreat!

491
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:20,333
[HELVI]
Hear that, Trandorkis? Our turn!

492
00:22:26,458 --> 00:22:27,916
[ERNESTI] It's strange.
There shouldn't be

